WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Make a new folder and open it in Visual Studio Code or your favourite IDE

2
00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:32.000
Fork your own copy of rhildred/browserBlog to your account

3
00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Copy the HTTPS url under the Code button

4
00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:53.000
Open a new terminal and run "git clone <copied url here> ."

5
00:00:54.000 --> 00:01:00.000
Run "npx http-server" (you will need to install node.js for this to work)

6
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:10.000
Surf to http://localhost:8080

7
00:01:20.000 --> 00:02:20.000
Add, edit, and delete the files until you are happy with the results. Here I'm using old files to save time.

8
00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:30.000
In a new terminal, type in "git add -A"

9
00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:40.000
Type in "git commit -m "your comment""

10
00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:55.000
type in "git push origin master --force"

11
00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:20.000
Click on the Settings tab on your repository

12
00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:33.000
Scroll down to GitHub Pages, select the master branch under Source, then hit Save

13
00:03:52.000 --> 00:04:01.000
Your portfolio is now published!
